{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thoroughly explore the repository at /home/agent/workspace to understand its current state. I need to compare against what CLAUDE.md claims. Specifically investigate:\n\n1. **Makefile** - Read the full Makefile and list all targets with their commands\n2. **internal/ directory** - List all subdirectories under internal/ and briefly describe each module (key files, main types/interfaces)\n3. **docker/ directory** - What's in it? Is entrypoint.sh still there? What does it do?\n4. **API router** - Find the chi router setup and list all routes/endpoints\n5. **Store interface** - Find the Store interface definition and list all methods\n6. **Notifier interface** - Find the Notifier interface definition\n7. **Models** - Find Task and Instance models, list their status enums\n8. **Config** - Find config struct, list all config fields and their env var names\n9. **Auth modes** - Check if api_key and max_subscription auth modes exist and how they work\n10. **Task ID format** - Verify ULID with bf_ prefix\n11. **Logging** - Verify zerolog usage\n12. **Database** - Check SQLite setup, WAL mode, migration approach in sqlite.go\n13. **Orchestrator** - Check polling interval, EC2 scaling, Docker via SSM, spot interruption handling\n14. **Port** - Verify the API runs on :8080\n15. **Any new modules or features** not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\nRead all relevant files and provide detailed findings for each area."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_015W9rgrmaZu78aSJETJC1Gh","session_id":"13b20e59-6472-468f-b07a-3e492441f548","uuid":"a9270cf1-9ff2-4d0a-b752-b93053355be0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R3CKXsVR7eWvSpQeurm98V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→## What This Is\n     4→\n     5→Backflow is a Go service that runs Claude Code in ephemeral Docker containers on AWS EC2 spot instances. Tasks come in via REST API; the orchestrator provisions infrastructure, runs agents, and cleans up.\n     6→\n     7→## Commands\n     8→\n     9→```bash\n    10→make build          # Build to bin/backflow\n    11→make run            # Build + run (sources .env)\n    12→make test           # go test ./... -v -count=1\n    13→make lint           # go vet ./...\n    14→make deps           # go mod tidy\n    15→make db-status      # Dump SQLite state\n    16→make docker-deploy  # Build + push agent image to ECR\n    17→make setup-aws      # Create AWS infrastructure\n    18→```\n    19→\n    20→Single test: `go test ./internal/store/ -run TestCreateTask -v`\n    21→\n    22→## Architecture\n    23→\n    24→Two goroutines: chi REST API on `:8080` + polling orchestrator (5s default).\n    25→\n    26→**Flow:** Client → API → SQLite → Orchestrator → Docker on EC2 via SSM → Webhooks.\n    27→\n    28→### Key modules (`internal/`)\n    29→\n    30→- **api/** — chi router, handlers, JSON responses\n    31→- **orchestrator/** — Poll loop, EC2 scaling, Docker via SSM, spot interruption handling\n    32→- **store/** — `Store` interface + SQLite (WAL mode, auto-migrated)\n    33→- **models/** — `Task` and `Instance` structs with status enums\n    34→- **config/** — Env-var config (`BACKFLOW_*` prefix)\n    35→- **notify/** — Webhook notifier\n    36→\n    37→### Agent container (`docker/`)\n    38→\n    39→Node.js image with Claude Code CLI + git + gh. `entrypoint.sh`: clone → checkout → run Claude → commit → push → create PR. Writes `status.json` for the orchestrator.\n    40→\n    41→### Statuses\n    42→\n    43→- **Task:** `pending` → `provisioning` → `running` → `completed` | `failed` | `interrupted` | `cancelled`\n    44→- **Instance:** `pending` → `running` → `draining` → `terminated`\n    45→\n    46→## Auth modes\n    47→\n    48→- **`api_key`** — Anthropic API key, concurrent agents\n    49→- **`max_subscription`** — Claude Max, serial (one agent at a time)\n    50→\n    51→## Design patterns\n    52→\n    53→- Interface abstractions (`Store`, `Notifier`) for testability\n    54→- Polling over events for simplicity\n    55→- SSM instead of SSH (no key management)\n    56→- ULID task IDs with `bf_` prefix\n    57→- Zerolog structured logging\n    58→\n    59→## Database\n    60→\n    61→SQLite with WAL mode. Schema auto-migrates on startup via `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` in `internal/store/sqlite.go:migrate()`. No separate migration files — add new columns with `ALTER TABLE` idempotently in the same function.\n    62→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13b20e59-6472-468f-b07a-3e492441f548","uuid":"59c2592c-a337-40ed-9310-bf36e1454c96","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/agent/workspace/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\n## What This Is\n\nBackflow is a Go service that runs Claude Code in ephemeral Docker containers on AWS EC2 spot instances. Tasks come in via REST API; the orchestrator provisions infrastructure, runs agents, and cleans up.\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\nmake build          # Build to bin/backflow\nmake run            # Build + run (sources .env)\nmake test           # go test ./... -v -count=1\nmake lint           # go vet ./...\nmake deps           # go mod tidy\nmake db-status      # Dump SQLite state\nmake docker-deploy  # Build + push agent image to ECR\nmake setup-aws      # Create AWS infrastructure\n```\n\nSingle test: `go test ./internal/store/ -run TestCreateTask -v`\n\n## Architecture\n\nTwo goroutines: chi REST API on `:8080` + polling orchestrator (5s default).\n\n**Flow:** Client → API → SQLite → Orchestrator → Docker on EC2 via SSM → Webhooks.\n\n### Key modules (`internal/`)\n\n- **api/** — chi router, handlers, JSON responses\n- **orchestrator/** — Poll loop, EC2 scaling, Docker via SSM, spot interruption handling\n- **store/** — `Store` interface + SQLite (WAL mode, auto-migrated)\n- **models/** — `Task` and `Instance` structs with status enums\n- **config/** — Env-var config (`BACKFLOW_*` prefix)\n- **notify/** — Webhook notifier\n\n### Agent container (`docker/`)\n\nNode.js image with Claude Code CLI + git + gh. `entrypoint.sh`: clone → checkout → run Claude → commit → push → create PR. Writes `status.json` for the orchestrator.\n\n### Statuses\n\n- **Task:** `pending` → `provisioning` → `running` → `completed` | `failed` | `interrupted` | `cancelled`\n- **Instance:** `pending` → `running` → `draining` → `terminated`\n\n## Auth modes\n\n- **`api_key`** — Anthropic API key, concurrent agents\n- **`max_subscription`** — Claude Max, serial (one agent at a time)\n\n## Design patterns\n\n- Interface abstractions (`Store`, `Notifier`) for testability\n- Polling over events for simplicity\n- SSM instead of SSH (no key management)\n- ULID task IDs with `bf_` prefix\n- Zerolog structured logging\n\n## Database\n\nSQLite with WAL mode. Schema auto-migrates on startup via `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` in `internal/store/sqlite.go:migrate()`. No separate migration files — add new columns with `ALTER TABLE` idempotently in the same function.\n","numLines":62,"startLine":1,"totalLines":62}}}
