{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015W9rgrmaZu78aSJETJC1Gh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile my detailed findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Repository Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Backflow repository and compared it against the claims in CLAUDE.md. Here are my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. **Makefile** - All targets confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/Makefile`\n\nAll targets mentioned in CLAUDE.md are present:\n- `make build` → Builds to `bin/backflow`\n- `make run` → Build + run (sources .env)\n- `make test` → `go test ./... -v -count=1`\n- `make lint` → `go vet ./...`\n- `make clean` → Removes `bin/` directory\n- `make db-status` → Bash script in `scripts/db-status.sh`\n- `make docker-build` → Buildx multi-platform build\n- `make docker-build-local` → Single-architecture build\n- `make docker-push` → Push to ECR\n- `make docker-deploy` → Complete ECR pipeline\n- `make setup-aws` → Bash script in `scripts/setup-aws.sh`\n- `make deps` → `go mod tidy`\n\n### 2. **internal/ directory structure** - All modules present\n**Path:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/`\n\nSubdirectories with descriptions:\n\n- **api/** - Chi REST API server\n  - `server.go` - Chi router setup with middleware\n  - `handlers.go` - Request handlers (CreateTask, GetTask, ListTasks, DeleteTask, GetTaskLogs, HealthCheck)\n  - `handlers_test.go` - Handler tests\n  - `responses.go` - JSON response helpers\n\n- **config/** - Environment variable configuration\n  - `config.go` - Config struct with env var loading (BACKFLOW_* prefix)\n\n- **models/** - Data structures\n  - `task.go` - Task model with status enums and CreateTaskRequest\n  - `instance.go` - Instance model with status enums\n  - `task_test.go` - Task tests\n\n- **store/** - Data persistence abstraction\n  - `store.go` - Store interface definition\n  - `sqlite.go` - SQLite implementation with WAL mode\n  - `sqlite_test.go` - Store tests\n\n- **notify/** - Event notifications\n  - `webhook.go` - Notifier interface and WebhookNotifier implementation\n\n- **orchestrator/** - Task orchestration and scaling\n  - `orchestrator.go` - Main orchestrator with polling\n  - `docker.go` - DockerManager for running agents via SSM/local\n  - `ec2.go` - EC2Manager for spot instance management\n  - `scaler.go` - EC2 scaling logic with SSM readiness checks\n  - `spot.go` - Spot interruption detection and task re-queuing\n  - `local.go` - Local mode scaler (no-op)\n\n### 3. **docker/ directory** - Confirmed presence\n**Path:** `/home/agent/workspace/docker/`\n\n- **Dockerfile** - Node.js 20 slim image with:\n  - Git, curl, jq, openssh-client\n  - GitHub CLI\n  - Claude Code CLI (npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-code)\n  - Agent user creation\n  - Global git config\n  - entrypoint.sh COPY and chmod\n\n- **entrypoint.sh** - Full implementation with:\n  - Repository cloning with depth 50\n  - Branch creation and checkout\n  - CLAUDE.md injection\n  - GitHub authentication setup\n  - Claude Code invocation with retries (MAX_RETRIES=3)\n  - Auth mode handling (api_key and max_subscription)\n  - PR creation with optional title/body generation\n  - Self-review phase with budget capping (20% of coding budget)\n  - Status file writing (status.json)\n  - Stream-json output parsing\n  - Needs-input detection\n\n### 4. **API Router** - Chi setup confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/server.go`\n\nRoutes under `/api/v1`:\n- `GET /health` - Health check endpoint\n- `POST /tasks` - Create task\n- `GET /tasks` - List tasks (with status, limit, offset filters)\n- `GET /tasks/{id}` - Get single task\n- `DELETE /tasks/{id}` - Delete/cancel task\n- `GET /tasks/{id}/logs` - Stream container logs\n\nMiddleware used: RequestID, RealIP, Logger, Recoverer, Content-Type header\n\n### 5. **Store Interface** - Fully defined\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n  // Tasks\n  CreateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error\n  GetTask(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Task, error)\n  ListTasks(ctx context.Context, filter TaskFilter) ([]*models.Task, error)\n  UpdateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error\n  DeleteTask(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n  \n  // Instances\n  CreateInstance(ctx context.Context, inst *models.Instance) error\n  GetInstance(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Instance, error)\n  ListInstances(ctx context.Context, status *models.InstanceStatus) ([]*models.Instance, error)\n  UpdateInstance(ctx context.Context, inst *models.Instance) error\n  \n  Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Notifier Interface** - Confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/notify/webhook.go`\n\n```go\ntype Notifier interface {\n  Notify(event Event) error\n}\n```\n\nImplementations:\n- `NoopNotifier` - discards all events\n- `WebhookNotifier` - HTTP POST with 3 retries, 10s timeout, event filtering\n\nEvent types: `task.created`, `task.running`, `task.completed`, `task.failed`, `task.needs_input`, `task.interrupted`\n\n### 7. **Models** - Status enums confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/models/`\n\n**Task Status:**\n- `pending` → `provisioning` → `running` → `completed` | `failed` | `interrupted` | `cancelled`\n- Method: `IsTerminal()` returns true for completed, failed, cancelled\n\n**Instance Status:**\n- `pending` → `running` → `draining` → `terminated`\n\nTask fields include: ID, Status, RepoURL, Branch, TargetBranch, Prompt, Context, Model, Effort, MaxBudgetUSD, MaxRuntimeMin, MaxTurns, CreatePR, SelfReview, PRTitle, PRBody, PRURL, AllowedTools, ClaudeMD, EnvVars, InstanceID, ContainerID, RetryCount, CostUSD, Error, timestamps\n\n### 8. **Config** - All fields present\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n  // Mode: ModeEC2 or ModeLocal\n  Mode Mode\n  \n  // Server\n  ListenAddr string // default: :8080\n  \n  // Auth\n  AuthMode AuthMode // api_key or max_subscription\n  AnthropicAPIKey string // ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n  ClaudeCredentialsPath string // CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH\n  \n  // AWS\n  AWSRegion string // AWS_REGION (default: us-east-1)\n  InstanceType string // BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE (default: t4g.medium)\n  AMI string // BACKFLOW_AMI\n  MaxInstances int // BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES (default: 5)\n  ContainersPerInst int // BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE (default: 4)\n  LaunchTemplateID string // BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID\n  \n  // Agent defaults\n  DefaultModel string // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL (default: claude-sonnet-4-6)\n  DefaultEffort string // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT (default: high)\n  DefaultMaxBudget float64 // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_BUDGET (default: 10.0)\n  DefaultMaxRuntime time.Duration // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_RUNTIME_MIN (default: 30 min)\n  DefaultMaxTurns int // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS (default: 200)\n  \n  // GitHub\n  GitHubToken string // GITHUB_TOKEN\n  \n  // Webhooks\n  WebhookURL string // BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL\n  WebhookEvents []string // BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS (comma-separated)\n  \n  // Database\n  DBPath string // BACKFLOW_DB_PATH (default: backflow.db)\n  \n  // Orchestrator\n  PollInterval time.Duration // BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC (default: 5s)\n}\n\n// MaxConcurrent() returns 1 if max_subscription mode, else max_instances * containers_per_inst\n```\n\n### 9. **Auth Modes** - Both exist and implemented\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n  AuthModeAPIKey AuthMode = \"api_key\"\n  AuthModeMaxSubscription AuthMode = \"max_subscription\"\n)\n```\n\n**API key mode:**\n- Requires `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable\n- Allows concurrent agents (MaxConcurrent = MaxInstances × ContainersPerInst)\n- Supports `--max-budget-usd` flag in Claude Code\n\n**Max subscription mode:**\n- Uses `CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH` for ~/.claude credentials volume mount\n- Serial execution (MaxConcurrent = 1)\n- No per-token billing (single seat)\n\nImplementation in docker.go: Uses different volume mount and env vars per mode\n\n### 10. **Task ID Format** - ULID with bf_ prefix confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers.go:46`\n\n```go\nID: \"bf_\" + ulid.Make().String(),\n```\n\nCreates task IDs like: `bf_<64-char-ulid>`\n\n### 11. **Logging** - Zerolog used\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go:21-23`\n\n```go\nlog.Logger = zerolog.New(zerolog.ConsoleWriter{Out: os.Stderr, TimeFormat: time.RFC3339}).\n  With().Timestamp().Caller().Logger()\n```\n\nStructured logging with timestamps and caller info throughout codebase\n\n### 12. **Database** - SQLite with WAL mode confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite.go`\n\n**WAL mode setup (line 21):**\n```go\nsql.Open(\"sqlite3\", dbPath+\"?_journal_mode=WAL&_busy_timeout=5000&_foreign_keys=on\")\n```\n\n**Migration approach (line 37-89):**\n- `migrate()` called on init\n- Creates two tables: `tasks` and `instances` with indices\n- Uses `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` for idempotency\n- Auto-migrates on startup\n\n**Schema includes:**\n- tasks table: 29 columns (all from Task model)\n- instances table: 9 columns (all from Instance model)\n- Indices on status and created_at\n\n### 13. **Orchestrator** - Full implementation verified\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`\n\n**Polling structure:**\n- Ticker with configurable interval (default 5 seconds, BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC)\n- Per-tick operations:\n  1. `monitorRunning()` - Check running tasks for timeout/completion\n  2. `dispatchPending()` - Assign pending tasks to instances\n  3. `scaler.Evaluate()` - Scale up/down EC2 instances\n\n**EC2 Scaling (orchestrator/scaler.go):**\n- LaunchSpotInstance() for spot instance provisioning\n- Reconcile pending instances (wait for SSM + Docker readiness)\n- Scale down idle instances (5 minute timeout)\n- RequestScaleUp() when no capacity\n\n**Docker via SSM (orchestrator/docker.go):**\n- RunAgent() - Sends docker run command via SSM\n- InspectContainer() - Gets container status/logs\n- StopContainer() - Graceful shutdown\n- Dual mode: local (bash exec) or EC2 (AWS SSM)\n\n**Spot Interruption Handling (orchestrator/spot.go):**\n- CheckInterruptions() - Polls for spot termination notices\n- Marks instance as draining\n- Re-queues running tasks back to pending status\n- Increments RetryCount\n\n### 14. **Port** - API runs on :8080 confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go:47`\n\n```go\nAddr: cfg.ListenAddr, // default: \":8080\"\n```\n\nAlso configurable via `BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR` environment variable\n\n### 15. **New/Additional Features Found**\n\n1. **Self-Review Phase** (entrypoint.sh:242-305)\n   - Enabled when `SELF_REVIEW=true` and PR created successfully\n   - Reviews PR diff and description\n   - Caps budget at 20% of coding budget (minimum $2)\n   - Posts review as PR comment\n   - Not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\n2. **Task Cancellation Handling** (api/handlers.go:135-141)\n   - DELETE endpoint supports cancelling running/provisioning tasks\n   - Status changed to `TaskStatusCancelled` instead of deletion\n   - Orchestrator kills container on next tick\n\n3. **LogFetcher Interface** (api/handlers.go:18-21)\n   - Required abstraction for getting container logs\n   - Implemented by DockerManager\n\n4. **TaskFilter Structure** (store/store.go:9-14)\n   - Supports filtering by Status, Limit, Offset for pagination\n\n5. **Retry Logic in entrypoint.sh** (lines 157-194)\n   - Retries Claude Code up to 3 times on failure\n   - Appends error context to prompt on retry\n   - Not persisted in orchestrator (no auto-retry on spot interruption beyond re-queue)\n\n6. **Stream-JSON Output Format** (entrypoint.sh:147, 198)\n   - Claude Code uses `--output-format stream-json`\n   - Parses result lines for completion detection\n   - Looks for `needs_input`, `is_error`, `error_type` fields\n\n7. **Instance Readiness Checks** (scaler.go:51-78)\n   - Waits for SSM agent to be online\n   - Checks Docker image availability before marking running\n   - Prevents premature task dispatch\n\n8. **Container Resource Limits** (docker.go:102)\n   - `--cpus=1 --memory=3g` hardcoded for agent containers\n\n9. **PR Title Auto-Generation** (entrypoint.sh:97)\n   - If `CREATE_PR=true` but no `PR_TITLE` provided\n   - Instructs agent to \"generate a concise, descriptive title\"\n\n10. **Schema Documentation** (docs/schema.md, docs/file-reference.md)\n    - Schema documentation exists (8.9 KB)\n    - File reference guide exists (5.0 KB)\n    - Not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe repository **closely matches** CLAUDE.md's description with the following confirmations:\n\n✅ Two goroutines (REST API + polling orchestrator)  \n✅ Chi router on :8080  \n✅ SQLite with WAL mode and auto-migration  \n✅ ULID task IDs with bf_ prefix  \n✅ Zerolog structured logging  \n✅ Interface-based design (Store, Notifier)  \n✅ Polling orchestrator with 5s default interval  \n✅ EC2 spot instance scaling  \n✅ Docker via SSM for remote execution  \n✅ Spot interruption handling with task re-queueing  \n✅ Both api_key and max_subscription auth modes  \n✅ Task status flow: pending → provisioning → running → terminal states  \n✅ Instance status flow: pending → running → draining → terminated  \n\n**Key additions not in CLAUDE.md:**\n- Self-review phase in agent entrypoint\n- Task cancellation endpoints\n- Comprehensive instance readiness checks\n- Schema and file reference documentation\n- Stream-json output handling for Claude Code\n\nAll file paths are absolute and tested in the exploration."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a922e22bf95ee341e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60282\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 95528</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13b20e59-6472-468f-b07a-3e492441f548","uuid":"09898638-2924-4da9-8f2f-cf056d42582b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the repository at /home/agent/workspace to understand its current state. I need to compare against what CLAUDE.md claims. Specifically investigate:\n\n1. **Makefile** - Read the full Makefile and list all targets with their commands\n2. **internal/ directory** - List all subdirectories under internal/ and briefly describe each module (key files, main types/interfaces)\n3. **docker/ directory** - What's in it? Is entrypoint.sh still there? What does it do?\n4. **API router** - Find the chi router setup and list all routes/endpoints\n5. **Store interface** - Find the Store interface definition and list all methods\n6. **Notifier interface** - Find the Notifier interface definition\n7. **Models** - Find Task and Instance models, list their status enums\n8. **Config** - Find config struct, list all config fields and their env var names\n9. **Auth modes** - Check if api_key and max_subscription auth modes exist and how they work\n10. **Task ID format** - Verify ULID with bf_ prefix\n11. **Logging** - Verify zerolog usage\n12. **Database** - Check SQLite setup, WAL mode, migration approach in sqlite.go\n13. **Orchestrator** - Check polling interval, EC2 scaling, Docker via SSM, spot interruption handling\n14. **Port** - Verify the API runs on :8080\n15. **Any new modules or features** not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\nRead all relevant files and provide detailed findings for each area.","agentId":"a922e22bf95ee341e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile my detailed findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Repository Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Backflow repository and compared it against the claims in CLAUDE.md. Here are my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. **Makefile** - All targets confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/Makefile`\n\nAll targets mentioned in CLAUDE.md are present:\n- `make build` → Builds to `bin/backflow`\n- `make run` → Build + run (sources .env)\n- `make test` → `go test ./... -v -count=1`\n- `make lint` → `go vet ./...`\n- `make clean` → Removes `bin/` directory\n- `make db-status` → Bash script in `scripts/db-status.sh`\n- `make docker-build` → Buildx multi-platform build\n- `make docker-build-local` → Single-architecture build\n- `make docker-push` → Push to ECR\n- `make docker-deploy` → Complete ECR pipeline\n- `make setup-aws` → Bash script in `scripts/setup-aws.sh`\n- `make deps` → `go mod tidy`\n\n### 2. **internal/ directory structure** - All modules present\n**Path:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/`\n\nSubdirectories with descriptions:\n\n- **api/** - Chi REST API server\n  - `server.go` - Chi router setup with middleware\n  - `handlers.go` - Request handlers (CreateTask, GetTask, ListTasks, DeleteTask, GetTaskLogs, HealthCheck)\n  - `handlers_test.go` - Handler tests\n  - `responses.go` - JSON response helpers\n\n- **config/** - Environment variable configuration\n  - `config.go` - Config struct with env var loading (BACKFLOW_* prefix)\n\n- **models/** - Data structures\n  - `task.go` - Task model with status enums and CreateTaskRequest\n  - `instance.go` - Instance model with status enums\n  - `task_test.go` - Task tests\n\n- **store/** - Data persistence abstraction\n  - `store.go` - Store interface definition\n  - `sqlite.go` - SQLite implementation with WAL mode\n  - `sqlite_test.go` - Store tests\n\n- **notify/** - Event notifications\n  - `webhook.go` - Notifier interface and WebhookNotifier implementation\n\n- **orchestrator/** - Task orchestration and scaling\n  - `orchestrator.go` - Main orchestrator with polling\n  - `docker.go` - DockerManager for running agents via SSM/local\n  - `ec2.go` - EC2Manager for spot instance management\n  - `scaler.go` - EC2 scaling logic with SSM readiness checks\n  - `spot.go` - Spot interruption detection and task re-queuing\n  - `local.go` - Local mode scaler (no-op)\n\n### 3. **docker/ directory** - Confirmed presence\n**Path:** `/home/agent/workspace/docker/`\n\n- **Dockerfile** - Node.js 20 slim image with:\n  - Git, curl, jq, openssh-client\n  - GitHub CLI\n  - Claude Code CLI (npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-code)\n  - Agent user creation\n  - Global git config\n  - entrypoint.sh COPY and chmod\n\n- **entrypoint.sh** - Full implementation with:\n  - Repository cloning with depth 50\n  - Branch creation and checkout\n  - CLAUDE.md injection\n  - GitHub authentication setup\n  - Claude Code invocation with retries (MAX_RETRIES=3)\n  - Auth mode handling (api_key and max_subscription)\n  - PR creation with optional title/body generation\n  - Self-review phase with budget capping (20% of coding budget)\n  - Status file writing (status.json)\n  - Stream-json output parsing\n  - Needs-input detection\n\n### 4. **API Router** - Chi setup confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/server.go`\n\nRoutes under `/api/v1`:\n- `GET /health` - Health check endpoint\n- `POST /tasks` - Create task\n- `GET /tasks` - List tasks (with status, limit, offset filters)\n- `GET /tasks/{id}` - Get single task\n- `DELETE /tasks/{id}` - Delete/cancel task\n- `GET /tasks/{id}/logs` - Stream container logs\n\nMiddleware used: RequestID, RealIP, Logger, Recoverer, Content-Type header\n\n### 5. **Store Interface** - Fully defined\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n  // Tasks\n  CreateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error\n  GetTask(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Task, error)\n  ListTasks(ctx context.Context, filter TaskFilter) ([]*models.Task, error)\n  UpdateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error\n  DeleteTask(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n  \n  // Instances\n  CreateInstance(ctx context.Context, inst *models.Instance) error\n  GetInstance(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Instance, error)\n  ListInstances(ctx context.Context, status *models.InstanceStatus) ([]*models.Instance, error)\n  UpdateInstance(ctx context.Context, inst *models.Instance) error\n  \n  Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Notifier Interface** - Confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/notify/webhook.go`\n\n```go\ntype Notifier interface {\n  Notify(event Event) error\n}\n```\n\nImplementations:\n- `NoopNotifier` - discards all events\n- `WebhookNotifier` - HTTP POST with 3 retries, 10s timeout, event filtering\n\nEvent types: `task.created`, `task.running`, `task.completed`, `task.failed`, `task.needs_input`, `task.interrupted`\n\n### 7. **Models** - Status enums confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/models/`\n\n**Task Status:**\n- `pending` → `provisioning` → `running` → `completed` | `failed` | `interrupted` | `cancelled`\n- Method: `IsTerminal()` returns true for completed, failed, cancelled\n\n**Instance Status:**\n- `pending` → `running` → `draining` → `terminated`\n\nTask fields include: ID, Status, RepoURL, Branch, TargetBranch, Prompt, Context, Model, Effort, MaxBudgetUSD, MaxRuntimeMin, MaxTurns, CreatePR, SelfReview, PRTitle, PRBody, PRURL, AllowedTools, ClaudeMD, EnvVars, InstanceID, ContainerID, RetryCount, CostUSD, Error, timestamps\n\n### 8. **Config** - All fields present\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n  // Mode: ModeEC2 or ModeLocal\n  Mode Mode\n  \n  // Server\n  ListenAddr string // default: :8080\n  \n  // Auth\n  AuthMode AuthMode // api_key or max_subscription\n  AnthropicAPIKey string // ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n  ClaudeCredentialsPath string // CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH\n  \n  // AWS\n  AWSRegion string // AWS_REGION (default: us-east-1)\n  InstanceType string // BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE (default: t4g.medium)\n  AMI string // BACKFLOW_AMI\n  MaxInstances int // BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES (default: 5)\n  ContainersPerInst int // BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE (default: 4)\n  LaunchTemplateID string // BACKFLOW_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE_ID\n  \n  // Agent defaults\n  DefaultModel string // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL (default: claude-sonnet-4-6)\n  DefaultEffort string // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT (default: high)\n  DefaultMaxBudget float64 // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_BUDGET (default: 10.0)\n  DefaultMaxRuntime time.Duration // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_RUNTIME_MIN (default: 30 min)\n  DefaultMaxTurns int // BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS (default: 200)\n  \n  // GitHub\n  GitHubToken string // GITHUB_TOKEN\n  \n  // Webhooks\n  WebhookURL string // BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL\n  WebhookEvents []string // BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS (comma-separated)\n  \n  // Database\n  DBPath string // BACKFLOW_DB_PATH (default: backflow.db)\n  \n  // Orchestrator\n  PollInterval time.Duration // BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC (default: 5s)\n}\n\n// MaxConcurrent() returns 1 if max_subscription mode, else max_instances * containers_per_inst\n```\n\n### 9. **Auth Modes** - Both exist and implemented\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n  AuthModeAPIKey AuthMode = \"api_key\"\n  AuthModeMaxSubscription AuthMode = \"max_subscription\"\n)\n```\n\n**API key mode:**\n- Requires `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable\n- Allows concurrent agents (MaxConcurrent = MaxInstances × ContainersPerInst)\n- Supports `--max-budget-usd` flag in Claude Code\n\n**Max subscription mode:**\n- Uses `CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH` for ~/.claude credentials volume mount\n- Serial execution (MaxConcurrent = 1)\n- No per-token billing (single seat)\n\nImplementation in docker.go: Uses different volume mount and env vars per mode\n\n### 10. **Task ID Format** - ULID with bf_ prefix confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers.go:46`\n\n```go\nID: \"bf_\" + ulid.Make().String(),\n```\n\nCreates task IDs like: `bf_<64-char-ulid>`\n\n### 11. **Logging** - Zerolog used\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go:21-23`\n\n```go\nlog.Logger = zerolog.New(zerolog.ConsoleWriter{Out: os.Stderr, TimeFormat: time.RFC3339}).\n  With().Timestamp().Caller().Logger()\n```\n\nStructured logging with timestamps and caller info throughout codebase\n\n### 12. **Database** - SQLite with WAL mode confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite.go`\n\n**WAL mode setup (line 21):**\n```go\nsql.Open(\"sqlite3\", dbPath+\"?_journal_mode=WAL&_busy_timeout=5000&_foreign_keys=on\")\n```\n\n**Migration approach (line 37-89):**\n- `migrate()` called on init\n- Creates two tables: `tasks` and `instances` with indices\n- Uses `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` for idempotency\n- Auto-migrates on startup\n\n**Schema includes:**\n- tasks table: 29 columns (all from Task model)\n- instances table: 9 columns (all from Instance model)\n- Indices on status and created_at\n\n### 13. **Orchestrator** - Full implementation verified\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`\n\n**Polling structure:**\n- Ticker with configurable interval (default 5 seconds, BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC)\n- Per-tick operations:\n  1. `monitorRunning()` - Check running tasks for timeout/completion\n  2. `dispatchPending()` - Assign pending tasks to instances\n  3. `scaler.Evaluate()` - Scale up/down EC2 instances\n\n**EC2 Scaling (orchestrator/scaler.go):**\n- LaunchSpotInstance() for spot instance provisioning\n- Reconcile pending instances (wait for SSM + Docker readiness)\n- Scale down idle instances (5 minute timeout)\n- RequestScaleUp() when no capacity\n\n**Docker via SSM (orchestrator/docker.go):**\n- RunAgent() - Sends docker run command via SSM\n- InspectContainer() - Gets container status/logs\n- StopContainer() - Graceful shutdown\n- Dual mode: local (bash exec) or EC2 (AWS SSM)\n\n**Spot Interruption Handling (orchestrator/spot.go):**\n- CheckInterruptions() - Polls for spot termination notices\n- Marks instance as draining\n- Re-queues running tasks back to pending status\n- Increments RetryCount\n\n### 14. **Port** - API runs on :8080 confirmed\n**File:** `/home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go:47`\n\n```go\nAddr: cfg.ListenAddr, // default: \":8080\"\n```\n\nAlso configurable via `BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR` environment variable\n\n### 15. **New/Additional Features Found**\n\n1. **Self-Review Phase** (entrypoint.sh:242-305)\n   - Enabled when `SELF_REVIEW=true` and PR created successfully\n   - Reviews PR diff and description\n   - Caps budget at 20% of coding budget (minimum $2)\n   - Posts review as PR comment\n   - Not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\n2. **Task Cancellation Handling** (api/handlers.go:135-141)\n   - DELETE endpoint supports cancelling running/provisioning tasks\n   - Status changed to `TaskStatusCancelled` instead of deletion\n   - Orchestrator kills container on next tick\n\n3. **LogFetcher Interface** (api/handlers.go:18-21)\n   - Required abstraction for getting container logs\n   - Implemented by DockerManager\n\n4. **TaskFilter Structure** (store/store.go:9-14)\n   - Supports filtering by Status, Limit, Offset for pagination\n\n5. **Retry Logic in entrypoint.sh** (lines 157-194)\n   - Retries Claude Code up to 3 times on failure\n   - Appends error context to prompt on retry\n   - Not persisted in orchestrator (no auto-retry on spot interruption beyond re-queue)\n\n6. **Stream-JSON Output Format** (entrypoint.sh:147, 198)\n   - Claude Code uses `--output-format stream-json`\n   - Parses result lines for completion detection\n   - Looks for `needs_input`, `is_error`, `error_type` fields\n\n7. **Instance Readiness Checks** (scaler.go:51-78)\n   - Waits for SSM agent to be online\n   - Checks Docker image availability before marking running\n   - Prevents premature task dispatch\n\n8. **Container Resource Limits** (docker.go:102)\n   - `--cpus=1 --memory=3g` hardcoded for agent containers\n\n9. **PR Title Auto-Generation** (entrypoint.sh:97)\n   - If `CREATE_PR=true` but no `PR_TITLE` provided\n   - Instructs agent to \"generate a concise, descriptive title\"\n\n10. **Schema Documentation** (docs/schema.md, docs/file-reference.md)\n    - Schema documentation exists (8.9 KB)\n    - File reference guide exists (5.0 KB)\n    - Not mentioned in CLAUDE.md\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe repository **closely matches** CLAUDE.md's description with the following confirmations:\n\n✅ Two goroutines (REST API + polling orchestrator)  \n✅ Chi router on :8080  \n✅ SQLite with WAL mode and auto-migration  \n✅ ULID task IDs with bf_ prefix  \n✅ Zerolog structured logging  \n✅ Interface-based design (Store, Notifier)  \n✅ Polling orchestrator with 5s default interval  \n✅ EC2 spot instance scaling  \n✅ Docker via SSM for remote execution  \n✅ Spot interruption handling with task re-queueing  \n✅ Both api_key and max_subscription auth modes  \n✅ Task status flow: pending → provisioning → running → terminal states  \n✅ Instance status flow: pending → running → draining → terminated  \n\n**Key additions not in CLAUDE.md:**\n- Self-review phase in agent entrypoint\n- Task cancellation endpoints\n- Comprehensive instance readiness checks\n- Schema and file reference documentation\n- Stream-json output handling for Claude Code\n\nAll file paths are absolute and tested in the exploration."}],"totalDurationMs":95528,"totalTokens":60282,"totalToolUseCount":37,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2502,"cache_read_input_tokens":53709,"output_tokens":4065,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2502},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
